prcStep.stepDesc:
This feature class was created using the GPS locations of surveyed pipes on the boundary of Huntington Wildlife Forest. Art Brooks located 106 different surveyed pipes using a Trimble mapping grade GPS with 1-5 meter accuracy. Post processing of these points by Paul Schemko, SUNY-ESF, provided within 2 meter accuracy. All corners on the property were located by Art Brooks with the mapping grade GPS unit. A variety of recreation grade GPS units were used to collect point information on the survey pipes not located by Art Brooks. The accuracy of these pipes varies, but generally is within 10 meters.
All point data from the surveyed pipes was used to create a point feature class in Arc Map version 10. These points were used to create a boundary polygon feature by snapping the polygon to each surveyed pipe location.
